@node play "The game: Installation/Playing"

                             Installation

  The installation is very simple, just place "Geodesik" where you
want on your hard drive, floppy disk, Ram Disk, etc. No other files
or Libraries are needed. However, the game requires a 68020(+)
Amiga with Workbench 2.0 or higher.

                             How to play?

  The game board is a representation of a geode which consists of a
circular area where 32 crystals, of triangular shape, are placed
pointing toward the center, which is indicated by an asterisk.
Crystals can have 4 sizes: short, medium, tall and tallest. At the
right of the game area is the type of geode or more appropriately,
its stability level. Under this is a percentage of same size
crystals, which is a ratio of the highest number of same size
crystals compared to all crystals on the game board.

  To make a crystal grow,  click in the general area where it is
located, between the geode's center to the coloured edge at the
base of the crystal. When a crystal is at its tallest size, it will
stay that way, unless the game reduces its size...

  Each of the 4 levels of crystal stability is associated to one of
four colours used by the game. These colours will remain the same
for as long as the game is active. Depending on the game board's
crystal stability, when you make a crystal grow, an other crystal
may randomly increase or decrease in size. The lesser the stability,
the more chances there are that a crystal will change size.

  Continue the game until all crystals are all of the same size
(and the 'Same size crystals' indicator gets to 100%), whatever
the size of the crystals, as this will complete the game.

  You can restart the game and/or change the geode's crystal
stability by clicking on the 'New Game' button.

  Have fun!

  You can quit the game by clicking on the game window's close
button or by pressing on the 'Esc' key.

